duck: Titanosaurs (members of the groups Titanosauria or Titanosauroidea) were a diverse group of sauropod dinosaurs, which included Saltasaurus and Isisaurus.
Any of various plant-eating, amphibious sauropod dinosaurs of the genus Titanosaurus, common during the Cretaceous Period especially in South America.

See text }} 'Titanosaurs' (members of the groups 'Titanosauria' or
'Titanosauroidea') were a diverse group of sauropod dinosaurs, which included
[[Saltasaurus]] and [[Isisaurus]]. It includes some of the heaviest creatures
ever to walk the earth, such as [[Argentinosaurus]] and [[Puertasaurus]] —
which are believed to have weighed up to 90 tonnes (100 short tons).
Consequently, they were named titanosaurs in honor of the mythological Titans,
the early deities of Ancient Greece. Together with the brachiosaurids and
relatives, they make up the larger clade Titanosauriformes.
